#pandas is a python library built on top of numpy that provides data structures and data analysis tools for working with structured data. It is widely used in data science and machine learning for tasks such as data cleaning, manipulation, and analysis. 
# Pandas provides two main data structures: Series (1-dimensional) and DataFrame (2-dimensional). 
# It also offers a wide range of functions for handling missing data, merging and joining datasets, and performing various operations on the data. 
# Overall, pandas is a powerful tool for working with structured data in Python.